Patient: What kind of exercise can I do at home?
Educator: You can do jumping jacks, stair climbing, or follow an exercise video online. 

Patient: But I don't have any exercise equipment.
Educator: You don't need equipment for these exercises. You can use your body weight. 

Patient: How often should I be exercising?
Educator: Aim for 30 minutes a day, five days a week. Start slow and gradually increase.

Patient: What if I can't do 30 minutes all at once?
Educator: No problem! Break it up. Do 10 minutes, three times a day.

Patient: What if I get tired quickly?
Educator: It's okay. Rest when you need to. With time, your stamina will improve.